HEADWORD: Water grass
<hw>Water grass</hw>. <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A tall march perennial grass
(<spn>Paspalum dilatatum</spn>) of the southern United States and the
American tropics.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Manna grass.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>The grass <spn>Chloris elegans</spn>.</def>
<sd>(d)</sd> <mark>[Dial. Eng.]</mark> (1) <def>Velvet grass.</def> (2)
<def>The water cress.</def> (3) <def>One of various
horsetails.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

